## Security

### Container Security
- Production images: non-root user (UID 1001)
- Shell and package managers removed in production (prevents RCE)
- Read-only root filesystem in Kubernetes
- Security contexts enforced (no privilege escalation, drop ALL capabilities)
{{ if .Computed.HasNode }}
### Node.js Security
- Helmet middleware for security headers
- CORS properly configured per environment
- Input validation with zod at API boundaries
- No `eval()`, `new Function()`, or dynamic requires
{{ end }}
### Kubernetes Security
- Pod security contexts: `runAsNonRoot: true`, `readOnlyRootFilesystem: true`
- ServiceAccount per service (least privilege)
- Network policies for service-to-service communication
{{ if hasItem .Project.Spec.Infrastructure.Components "external-secrets" }}
### Secrets Management
- External Secrets Operator syncs from cloud provider secret manager
- Never commit secrets to git
- Use `secretRef` in Helm values for sensitive configuration
{{ end }}
